E-hailing platform Bolt has launched a Women-Only service that enables female passengers to request rides from female drivers only. The request for a ride will not be visible to male drivers. Bolt South Africa Manager, Gareth Taylor spoke with eNCA's Jane Dutton. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - E-hailing platform, Bolt, has launched a Women-Only service that enables female passengers to request rides from female drivers only. READ: Taxify renamed to Bolt This service is currently available in a few cities and will be rolled out across the country. Bolt says this is just one of the ways to ensure the safety of women in the country. Watch the video above for more details on this story.